          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1.-1632836897108-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1.-1632836897108-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1.-1632836897108-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into rough, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender, then drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1632836903348-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1632836903348-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1632836903348-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1632836903348-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1632836903348-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the potatoes are cooking, reboil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>creamed</strong> <strong>coconut </strong>roughly (if required!), then dissolve it in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[380ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>with the<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> – this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1632836951496-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1632836951496-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1632836951496-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1632836951496-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1632836951496-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>ginger</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Add your <strong>garam masala</strong> and <strong>ground turmeric</strong> and cook for 30 secs further</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1632836979779-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1632836979779-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1632836979779-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1632836979779-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1632836979779-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Stir 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> into the pan, then add the <strong>coconut stock</strong> and increase the heat to medium-high</p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the <strong>spinach</strong> to the pan and cook for 5-8 min, stirring frequently or until it's wilted and the sauce has thickened to a curry-like consistency</p><p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>coriander </strong>finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1632836995687-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1632836995687-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1632836995687-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1632836995687-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1632836995687-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once thickened, remove the curry sauce from the heat, then drain your <strong>king prawns</strong> and add them to the pan with the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>coriander</strong> and <strong>haddock</strong> <strong>bites</strong> – this is your <strong>Indian-style haddock & king prawn pie mix</strong></p><p>Tip: Unevenly-sized haddock bites? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!</p><p>Transfer the <strong>Indian-style haddock & king prawn pie mix</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1632837018095-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1632837018095-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1632837018095-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1632837018095-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1632837018095-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the<strong> drained potatoes</strong> to a low heat and add your <strong>cumin seeds </strong>with<strong> </strong>a splash of <strong>milk</strong> and a large knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Mash until smooth and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Top the Indian-style haddock & prawn pie mix<strong> </strong>with the <strong>mash</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 15-20 min or until the mash is golden and the fish is cooked through – this is your <strong>Indian-style haddock & king prawn pie</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1632837038519-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1632837038519-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1632837038519-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1632837038519-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1632837038519-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once cooked, remove the pie from the oven and leave to stand for 5 min (this helps the flavours to develop and makes it easier to serve!)</p><p>Serve the <strong>Indian-style haddock & king prawn pie</strong> with the <strong>quick-pickled</strong> <strong>chilli </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle the <strong>pickling liquid</strong> all over for extra flavour (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
